  "why": "The paper does more than report failures: it links jailbreak-induced failures to concrete internal model behaviors and vulnerabilities. The authors perform clustering of hidden states, quantify neuron-coverage differences (Table IV), introduce RCG to measure layer/block sensitivity, and show that attack queries systematically activate different neurons (and blocks/attention layers) than normal queries. They explicitly attribute this to mechanisms such as safety-neuron bypass and activation of distinct knowledge-domain neurons, and they demonstrate these links with empirical results across models, layers, blocks, and tokens. These analyses explain why failures occur and point to concrete model internals that can be targeted for mitigation (e.g., attention layers, specific blocks, safety neurons), satisfying the metric requirement for diagnostic understanding of underlying vulnerabilities.",
